Nowadays it is only possible to:
* [Add users to project's default reviewer users list|https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/fecru.html#rest-service-fecru:admin:projects:key:default-reviewer-users] *one by one*
* [Add groups to project's default reviewer group list|https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/fecru.html#rest-service-fecru:admin:projects:key:default-reviewer-groups] *one by one*
* [Add users to project's allowed reviewer users list|https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/fecru.html#rest-service-fecru:admin:projects:key:allowed-reviewer-users] *one by one*
* [Add groups to project's allowed reviewer group list|https://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/fecru.html#rest-service-fecru:admin:projects:key:allowed-reviewer-groups] *one by one*

For all cases above, the parameter "name" should be used, like this:
{code}
{
  "name" : "value"
}
{code}

Supposing that someone needs to add a large number of users and groups, this might require a lot of manual work.

It would be much better and faster to call those REST resources only once, using an array of values for that parameter in the request. Something like this would work:
{code}
{
  "names" : [ {
    "name" : "value1"
  }, {
    "name" : "value2"
  }, {
    "name" : "value3"
  }, {
    "name" : "value4"
  } ]
}
{code}

Added paths to "FishEye Project Content" can't be removed, after selecting "Remove" from the *Actions* column the row does disappear, however navigating away from the page and then coming back reveals that the content is still present.

For Example;

I will remove */Search_Results/TestFold/*
!screen1.png|thumbnail!

This is now removed from the list
!screen2.png|thumbnail!

Navigating away from the page or selecting the Add Button with no value or a value results in the previously removed row returning;

!screen3.png|thumbnail!


*Work Around*

As a work around you can remove the entries for the paths directly from the database.

{panel:title=Warning|titleBGColor=#FFFFCE|bgColor=#FFFFCE}
Ensure that FishEye Crucible is shut down and that you make a database back up before making any alterations to the database.
{panel}

The entries are found in the table {{cru_content_root}}. As an example using PostgreSQL the following command was used to remove an entry;

{code:sql}
DELETE FROM cru_content_root WHERE cru_content_root_id = 1;
{code}

Using only Crucible if you try to add the latest revision of a file to a review it is already in but has comments on the section representing the last review the following error message is received;

!Screen Shot 2015-03-06 at 10.23.19.png|thumbnail!

....& in the logs;

{noformat}
2015-03-05 08:39:41,292 WARN  [qtp2052243497-13529 ] fisheye Review-removeFRXRevision - FRXRevision 709 has comments and cannot be deleted.
{noformat}

This only occurs when using adding in the following method;

# Add Content
# Explore Repositories
# Select Repo & then files
# Select the latest revision from the drop down for the file
# Error is shown

Adding the latest revision in the following way completes successfully;

# Add Content
# Browse Changesets
# Select the repo
# Select the tick box next to the revision wanting to be added
# New revision is added

Author mapping is failing with NPE when trying to add a mapping to a user and the same mapping is already defined for an inactive user.

{code}
Caused by: java.lang.NullPointerException
